Daily bit(e) of C++ #69, The C++11 ref-qualifiers for member functions With the introduction of r-value references, the C++11 standard also added ref-qualifiers for methods. This allows us to distinguish between situations when a method is invoked on an l-value and r-value object. If you dislike the resulting code duplication, look for the “deducing this” feature in C++23. struct MyClass {
    // mutable l-value
    void operation() & { }
    // prvalue or xvalue
    void operation() && { }
    // const l-value
    void operation() const& { }
};

const MyClass a;
a.operation();
// const l-value

MyClass b;
b.operation();
// mutable l-value

MyClass{}.operation();
// prvalue

std::move(b).operation();
// xvalue

